abstract: “Someone in the orchestra studied with someone who studied with someone who has played under Beethoven’s direction.”
snippet: “Someone in the orchestra studied with someone who studied with someone who has played under Beethoven’s direction.”
lead_paragraph: VIENNA — When the Vienna Philharmonic goes on tour next year with a cycle of Beethoven Symphonies, the musicians will not just commemorate the 250th anniversary of the composer’s birth. Recent research is revealing previously undisclosed connections between the composer and the orchestra’s founding members that stretch back over two centuries.

abstract: Experienced sailors say not to approach it as one event, but as several.
snippet: Experienced sailors say not to approach it as one event, but as several.
lead_paragraph: Sailboat races have a way of developing their own lore, especially when there are boat-breaking waves and fast-moving weather systems. It is easy to think that the annual Rolex Sydney Hobart Yacht Race, which begins on Thursday, involves just three things: the start, the spin cycle and the finish.

abstract: Change has come slowly for the Vienna Philharmonic, but there has been progress.
snippet: Change has come slowly for the Vienna Philharmonic, but there has been progress.
lead_paragraph: Women were first hired into a major orchestra in 1913, when six female violinists joined the Queen’s Hall Orchestra in London. But in Vienna, female musicians were not officially offered auditions to the philharmonic until more than eight decades later.

abstract: The yacht race is marking its 75th year, but nearby bush fires may hinder the party.
snippet: The yacht race is marking its 75th year, but nearby bush fires may hinder the party.
lead_paragraph: Hundreds of sailors this month are about to celebrate the 75th anniversary of the Rolex Sydney Hobart Yacht Race. Then one uninvited guest showed up: smoke from nearby bush fires.

abstract: An old tale about a children’s ward in 1891 may be a myth, but the diphtheria antitoxin was a real gift.
snippet: An old tale about a children’s ward in 1891 may be a myth, but the diphtheria antitoxin was a real gift.
lead_paragraph: Gather around, children, and let me tell you the — false — legend of the Christmas diphtheria antitoxin miracle. I’ve just finished a book about the end of many kinds of childhood mortality, and got caught up in this tale that is often said to have happened on Christmas 1891, in Berlin.

abstract: Body-wide inflammation is tied to most chronic diseases, limiting people’s health and longevity.
snippet: Body-wide inflammation is tied to most chronic diseases, limiting people’s health and longevity.
lead_paragraph: The quest for a fountain of youth is many centuries old and marred by many false starts and unfulfilled promises. But modern medical science is now gradually closing in on what might realistically enable people to live longer, healthier lives — if they are willing to sacrifice some popular hedonistic pleasures.

headline_main: Tackling Inflammation to Fight Age-Related Ailments

abstract: The proposal by Gov. Andrew Cuomo would make New York the second state to approve a ban on containers made of polystyrene.
snippet: The proposal by Gov. Andrew Cuomo would make New York the second state to approve a ban on containers made of polystyrene.
lead_paragraph: The previously ubiquitous puffy containers began to disappear this year from New York City delis, takeout joints and halal food trucks. They were banished from other pockets of the state as well, and in many cities around the world.

snippet: In New York, boutiques of all kinds are beginning to look a lot like cafes.

headline_main: Why Is There a Coffee Shop in So Many Stores?

abstract: A collection of long-lost Zora Neale Hurston stories, a heart-stopping novel about a migrant’s journey across Mexico, a look at the crisis facing America’s working class and more.
snippet: A collection of long-lost Zora Neale Hurston stories, a heart-stopping novel about a migrant’s journey across Mexico, a look at the crisis facing America’s working class and more.
lead_paragraph: Lydia, a bookstore owner, had a pleasant life in Acapulco before the arrival of a violent cartel called Los Jardineros. After her husband publishes an exposé about the group’s leader in the local newspaper, her family is massacred, and Lydia and her young son must go on the run. This novel is a heart-stopping story of survival, danger and love, as they undertake the grueling journey to the United States.
